12:27:13 DEBUG anthropic._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/v1/messages', 'headers': {'X-Stainless-Helper-Method': 'stream', 'X-Stainless-Stream-Helper': 'messages'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-afef60db-954a-4ebf-a1f2-875646906938', 'content': None, 'json_data': {'max_tokens': 4096, 'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Triage FortiSOAR alert `alerts:b62fb2d5-d27e-4d7e-8bd8-53e4878ba614` ("Excessive End User Mail from 192.168.77.10"). Pull the alert, extract the source and destination IPs, look for other recent alerts involving the same host, enrich any EXTERNAL (public) indicators with the threat-intel connectors, and give a short verdict on whether this is benign bulk mail or exfiltration. Stage any containment for analyst approval with emit_action_card rather than executing it.'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': [{'type': 'text', 'text': "I'll triage this alert systematically. Let me start by pulling the alert record, then extract the indicators and hunt for related activity."}, {'type': 'tool_use', 'id': 'toolu_01HmUoQM1EmJ6RVwC97QB4Bi', 'name': 'get_record', 'input': {'module': 'alerts', 'uuid': 'b62fb2d5-d27e-4d7e-8bd8-53e4878ba614', 'relationships': True}}]}, {'role': 'user', 'content': [{'type': 'tool_result', 'tool_use_id': 'toolu_01HmUoQM1EmJ6RVwC97QB4Bi', 'content': '{"ok": true, "iri": "/api/3/alerts/b62fb2d5-d27e-4d7e-8bd8-53e4878ba614", "url": "https://mfz9dldmc5b7hllc2rs.us-west-1.fortisoc.forticloud.com/api/3/alerts/b62fb2d5-d27e-4d7e-8bd8-53e4878ba614?$relationships=true", "record": {"@id": "/api/3/alerts/b62fb2d5-d27e-4d7e-8bd8-53e4878ba614", "detail": {"incidentCount": 20}, "reportingDeviceIP": "127.0.0.1", "subType": "Collection", "lastSeen": 1780139865, "firstSeen": 1780139865, "subcategory": "Collection", "ruleName": "Excessive End User Mail", "title": "Excessive End User Mail from 192.168.77.10", "reportingDeviceName": "localhost", "eventTime": "1780139865000", "destinationCountry": "